TITLE: Fix task system UI desync on proposal build failures — preserve self-healing
PRIORITY: high
TYPE: src_edit
SUMMARY: Proposal tasks with Anthropic models self-heal build errors successfully, but UI shows "paused" while agent continues. Fix: implement retry counter so agent can recover once (letting Claude self-fix), then pause if stuck. Preserves intelligent recovery, fixes UI desync.
FULL IMPLEMENTATION PLAN:
## Why this change

When a proposal task (src_edit) encounters a `npm run build` failure:

1. The SSE callback at line 541-551 detects the error
2. Calls `_pauseForAssistance()` to pause the task
3. But `_pauseForAssistance()` only returns from the callback, not the entire LLM round
4. Claude (Anthropic) sees the build error in the response, self-heals it, reruns build successfully
5. **UI shows "paused" while agent continues and completes the task in background**

This is an asymmetry: Anthropic is smart enough to fix the error, but the current code assumes all errors need human help.

**User preference:** Keep the self-healing behavior (it's great!), but fix the UI desync so the frontend shows accurate status.

---

## The fix approach

Replace the unconditional pause with a **retry counter**:

1. **First build failure:** Log it, increment counter, do NOT pause, let agent continue
2. **Second failure in same step:** Update status to 'recovering' (visual feedback), increment counter, continue
3. **Third failure:** Now pause with `needs_assistance` (agent is truly stuck)
4. **Reset counter** when any write/mutate tool fires (real progress made)

This way:
- Claude can self-heal on first try (preserves smart behavior)
- UI shows "running"/"recovering" (no false "paused" state)
- If agent gets stuck in loop, it pauses (safety fallback)
- Smaller models that can't self-fix will hit limit after 1st failure and pause correctly

---

## Exact source edits

### File: src/gateway/tasks/background-task-runner.ts

**Change 1: Add build failure tracking to the runtime state (line 502-503)**

```typescript
// ── Stall counter state ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Tracks tool calls since the last step_complete. At threshold, inject nudge.
let toolCallsSinceLastStepComplete = 0;
let stallNudgeInjected = false;
let buildFailureRetryCount = 0;  // NEW: Track build failures in current step
```

**Change 2: Reset build failure counter when write/mutate tools fire (line 511-515)**

In the MUTATE_TOOLS check:
```typescript
} else if (MUTATE_TOOLS.has(toolName)) {
  // Write/mutate tool fired — real progress, reset stall counter
  toolCallsSinceLastStepComplete = 0;
  stallNudgeInjected = false;
  buildFailureRetryCount = 0;  // NEW: Reset on real progress
```

**Change 3: Replace the pause-on-build-failure logic (line 541-552)**

OLD:
```typescript
if (data.error && _isProposalTask) {
  const action = String(data.action || '').toLowerCase();
  const result = String(data.result || '');
  const isBuildFailure =
    (action === 'run_command' && /npm\s+run\s+build|npm\s+run\s+tsc/.test(result) && /exit\s+[1-9]\d*|TIMED OUT/i.test(result)) ||
    (action === 'gateway_restart' && /build\s+failed|Build\s+FAILED/i.test(result));
  if (isBuildFailure) {
    const taskForPause = loadTask(taskId);
    if (taskForPause) this._pauseForAssistance(taskForPause, 'Build failed — TypeScript did not compile cleanly.', result.slice(-1500));
    return;
  }
}
```

NEW:
```typescript
if (data.error && _isProposalTask) {
  const action = String(data.action || '').toLowerCase();
  const result = String(data.result || '');
  const isBuildFailure =
    (action === 'run_command' && /npm\s+run\s+build|npm\s+run\s+tsc/.test(result) && /exit\s+[1-9]\d*|TIMED OUT/i.test(result)) ||
    (action === 'gateway_restart' && /build\s+failed|Build\s+FAILED/i.test(result));
  if (isBuildFailure) {
    buildFailureRetryCount++;
    const taskForStatusUpdate = loadTask(taskId);
    if (taskForStatusUpdate) {
      // First failure: log + let agent continue (self-healing attempt)
      if (buildFailureRetryCount === 1) {
        appendJournal(taskId, {
          type: 'error',
          content: `Build failed (attempt 1): ${result.slice(-200)}. Agent will attempt recovery.`,
        });
        // Do NOT pause — allow agent to self-heal
      } 
      // Second failure: show "recovering" status + continue
      else if (buildFailureRetryCount === 2) {
        appendJournal(taskId, {
          type: 'error',
          content: `Build failed again (attempt 2): ${result.slice(-200)}. Recovery in progress.`,
        });
        updateTaskStatus(taskId, 'running', { pauseReason: 'recovering_from_build_error' });
        this._broadcast('task_panel_update', { taskId });
        // Do NOT pause — agent gets one more chance
      } 
      // Third+ failure: genuinely stuck, pause for assistance
      else {
        appendJournal(taskId, {
          type: 'error',
          content: `Build failed ${buildFailureRetryCount} times. Pausing for assistance: ${result.slice(-500)}`,
          detail: result.slice(-1500),
        });
        this._pauseForAssistance(taskForStatusUpdate, `Build failed ${buildFailureRetryCount} times — unable to auto-recover.`, result.slice(-1500));
        return; // Only return here to stop SSE processing on actual pause
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Change 4: Reset build failure counter on step advancement (line 791-792)**

When step completes:
```typescript
if (reloadedTask.currentStepIndex !== liveTask.currentStepIndex) {
  // Agent called step_complete and step advanced — log it and continue
  appendJournal(taskId, {
    type: 'status_push',
    content: `Step advanced from ${liveTask.currentStepIndex + 1} to ${reloadedTask.currentStepIndex + 1} via step_complete.`,
  });
  toolCallsSinceLastStepComplete = 0;
  stallNudgeInjected = false;
  buildFailureRetryCount = 0;  // NEW: Reset for new step
```

